# Copy to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile (or run: caddy run --config /path/to/Caddyfile) after installing Caddy.
# Prerequisites:
#  - DNS A/AAAA record: your FQDN → this VM (JetStream floating IP)
#  - Security group: allow inbound TCP 80 and 443
#  - Kestrel profile ServerCaddy: only http://127.0.0.1:8081 (set CODIRA_LAUNCH_PROFILE=ServerCaddy in systemd)
#
# Replace the host line with your real domain, and set a real email (Let's Encrypt account / expiry notices).
{
	email you@institution.edu
}

your-app.example.edu {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8081
}

# Caddy issues and renews certificates automatically. Users hit https://your-app.example.edu — no PFX in Kestrel.
# The app already uses X-Forwarded-For / X-Forwarded-Proto (Program.cs) for this reverse-proxy case.
